import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_airports = data.groupby('origin').sum().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    top_10_airports.plot(kind='bar', y='count', legend=False)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of number of flights?')
    for i, count in enumerate(top_10_airports['count']):
        plt.text(i, count, str(count), ha='center', va='bottom')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of flights between airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot(index='origin', columns='destination', values='count')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 15))
    sns.heatmap(data, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='YlGnBu', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Destination Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_title('What are the most popular routes in terms of number of flights?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='count', data=data, color='lightblue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["count"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights per airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import math

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = np.sqrt((data['origin_latitude'] - data['destination_latitude']) ** 2 + (data['origin_longitude'] - data['destination_longitude']) ** 2)
    plt.scatter(data['count'], data['distance'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Distance between Airports')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of flights and distance between airports?')
    plt.grid(True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
